Part.Source: parm(in:&Title, in:&Text, in:&Type, in:&ControlSelector, in:&Hide, in:&IsDesktopNotification, in:&DesktopNotificationIconUrl, in:&ClickRedirectURL, out:&Parms);
&Parms = DVMessageGetAdvancedNotificationMsg(&Title, &Text, &Type, '', DVMessageBoolean.NoSpecify, DVMessageBoolean.True, &DesktopNotificationIconUrl, &ClickRedirectURL)
parm(in:&Title, in:&Text, in:&DesktopNotificationIconUrl, in:&ClickRedirectURL, out:&Parms);
&Parms = DVMessageGetAdvancedNotificationMsg(&Title, &Text, &Type, &ControlSelector, &Hide, DVMessageBoolean.False, '', &ClickRedirectURL)
parm(in:&Title, in:&Text, in:&Type, in:&ControlSelector, in:&Hide, in:&ClickRedirectURL, out:&Parms);

&UndoSecureText = &Text If &UndoSecureText.Length() > 0 AND (&UndoSecureText.StartsWith(!"'=") OR &UndoSecureText.StartsWith(!"'+") OR &UndoSecureText.StartsWith(!"'-") OR &UndoSecureText.StartsWith(!"'@")) &UndoSecureText = &UndoSecureText.Substring(2) EndIf
parm(in:&Text, out:&UndoSecureText);

Event Enter
&FilterToUploadExt = &FilterToUpload.FileName &FilterToUploadExt = iif(&FilterToUploadExt.IndexOf('.') > 0, &FilterToUploadExt.Substring(&FilterToUploadExt.LastIndexOf(".") + 1, &FilterToUploadExt.Length() - &FilterToUploadExt.LastIndexOf(".")),'') msg(!'<#CLEAR#>') If not &FilterToUpload.IsEmpty() If (&FilterToUploadExt.ToUpper() = !'CSV' and &ImportType = !'CSV') OR (&FilterToUploadExt.ToUpper() = !'XLSX' and &ImportType = !'Excel') &ResultMsg = '' If WWPBaseObjects.WWP_ImportData(&TransactionName, &ImportType, &FilterToUpload, &ExtraParmsJson, &ErrorMsgs) &LastErrorType = MessageTypes.Info For &Message in &ErrorMsgs If not &ResultMsg.IsEmpty() &ResultMsg += newline() If &LastErrorType = MessageTypes.Warning AND &Message.Type = MessageTypes.Info &ResultMsg += newline() EndIf EndIf &LastErrorType = &Message.Type &ResultMsg += &Message.Description EndFor msg(DVMessageGetBasicNotificationMsg('File import success', &ResultMsg, DVMessageType.success, '', DVMessageBoolean.NoSpecify, '')) &Ret = true Refresh Else &FilterToUpload.SetEmpty() For &Message in &ErrorMsgs If not &ResultMsg.IsEmpty() &ResultMsg += newline() If &Message.Id = !'WWP_LineId' &ResultMsg += newline() EndIf EndIf &ResultMsg += &Message.Description EndFor msg(DVMessageGetBasicNotificationMsg('Error importing file', &ResultMsg, DVMessageType.error, '', DVMessageBoolean.False, '')) EndIf Else &FilterToUpload.SetEmpty() &ResultMsg = format('The expected file type is %1.', iif(&ImportType = !'CSV',!'csv',!'xlsx')) msg(DVMessageGetBasicNotificationMsg('Invalid file type', &ResultMsg, DVMessageType.error, '', DVMessageBoolean.NoSpecify, '')) Endif Else msg(Format('WWP_RequiredAttribute','File')) EndIf
EndEvent
Event Refresh
If &Ret Return EndIf
EndEvent

&Message = new() &Message.Id = &MsgId &Message.Type = &MsgType &Message.Description = &MsgDsc
&Messages.Add(&Message)
parm(in:&MsgId, in:&MsgType, in:&MsgDsc, inout:&Messages);

If not &LineId.IsEmpty() WWP_AddMessage(!'WWP_LineId', MessageTypes.Info, format('File line: %1', &LineId), &Messages) EndIf
For &Message in &ErrorsToAdd If &Message.Type = MessageTypes.Error &Messages.Add(&Message) EndIf EndFor
parm(inout:&Messages, in:&LineId, in:&ErrorsToAdd);

/* Generated by DVelop Work With Plus Pattern [Start] - Do not change */
/* Generated by DVelop Work With Plus Pattern [End] - Do not change */
parm(in:&SelctionName, in:&ImportType, in:&FilePath, in:&ExtraParmsJson, out:&Messages, out:&IsOk);

&ColumIndexes = new()
&ColumnsLineSplitted = &ColumnsLineText.SplitRegEx(!';') &ColumnsCount = &ColumnsLineSplitted.Count
For &TitleName in &TitleNames &Index = &ColumnsLineSplitted.IndexOf(&TitleName) &ColumIndexes.Add(&Index) EndFor
&ColumnsFound = 0 &DiscardedColumns = '' For &i = 1 To &ColumnsLineSplitted.Count If &ColumIndexes.IndexOf(&i) = 0 If not &DiscardedColumns.IsEmpty() &DiscardedColumns += ', ' EndIf &DiscardedColumns += &ColumnsLineSplitted.Item(&i) Else &ColumnsFound += 1 EndIf EndFor
If &DiscardedColumns.Length() > 50 &DiscardedColumns = &DiscardedColumns.Substring(1, 50) &DiscardedColumns = &DiscardedColumns.Trim() + '...' EndIf
parm(in:&TitleNames, in:&ColumnsLineText, out:&DiscardedColumns, out:&ColumIndexes, out:&ColumnsCount, out:&ColumnsFound);

&ColumIndexes = new()
&ColumnsLineSplitted = new() &ContinueReading = True &ColIndex = 1 Do while &ContinueReading If &ExcelDocument.Cells(&LineNumber, &ColIndex).Text <> '' &ColumnsLineSplitted.Add(&ExcelDocument.Cells(&LineNumber, &ColIndex).Text) &ColIndex += 1 Else &ContinueReading = False EndIf EndDo
&ColumnsCount = &ColumnsLineSplitted.Count
For &TitleName in &TitleNames &Index = &ColumnsLineSplitted.IndexOf(&TitleName) &ColumIndexes.Add(&Index) EndFor
&ColumnsFound = 0 &DiscardedColumns = '' For &i = 1 To &ColumnsLineSplitted.Count If &ColumIndexes.IndexOf(&i) = 0 If not &DiscardedColumns.IsEmpty() &DiscardedColumns += ', ' EndIf &DiscardedColumns += &ColumnsLineSplitted.Item(&i) Else &ColumnsFound += 1 EndIf EndFor
If &DiscardedColumns.Length() > 50 &DiscardedColumns = &DiscardedColumns.Substring(1, 50) &DiscardedColumns = &DiscardedColumns.Trim() + '...' EndIf
parm(in:&TitleNames, in:&ExcelDocument, in:&LineNumber, out:&DiscardedColumns, out:&ColumIndexes, out:&ColumnsCount, out:&ColumnsFound);

If not &LineId.IsEmpty() WWP_AddMessage(!'WWP_LineId', MessageTypes.Info, format('File line: %1', &LineId), &Messages) EndIf
WWP_AddMessage(&ErrorToAddId, MessageTypes.Error, &ErrorToAddDsc, &Messages)
parm(inout:&Messages, in:&LineId, in:&ErrorToAddId, in:&ErrorToAddDsc);

EndEvent
